Over the next month you’ll probably have more guests than usual in your home. Here are a few hacks I use for when I’ve got guests visiting🥰

1. Essential oils come in a every scent imaginable now! Including Christmassy scents like snow fairy✨ a couple of drops in a spray bottle with water will leave your bathroom smelling incredible! Bonus tip: you can also add a few drops into your drains & behind your toilet for extra freshness.

These 3 things are causing odours in your kitchen!👀 

1. Dishwasher 
You would think that an appliance designed to clean wouldn’t be such a main culprit in causing odours but they do! Be sure to clean that filter every few days & run a bowl of white vinegar on a hot wash through it. 

2. Extractor Fan Filter 
Out of sign & out of mind… I had never paid mine much attention until I was cleaning the main fan one day and noticed the filter was covered in grease 🤢 a quick soak in washing up liquid and it will be as good as new! 

3. Drains! After seeing the first two it’s no surprise your drains can harbour germs and odours especially with how much gets washed down then - bicarb and a disinfectant with some warm water daily will keep them smelling fresh 🌼

Ps. The slide is back in action 😉 🏃🏼‍♀️

Anyone who lives in a hard water area knows the struggle of never ending limescale! Over the years I’ve tried so many different methods but I wanted to show my three most popular: 

🍋 Grab that leftover lemon juice from pancake day! Cover the base of your kettle & add water. Boil & the limescale will be gone. 

🫧 Pre made descaler! If you don’t want to bother with the natural methods a descaler is always an option. Follow the instructions on the back to suit your appliance. 

🧽 White vinegar is a fan favourite it has so many uses including descaling. Pop neat into a spray bottle & spray all those hard to reach areas around the sink - leave it for 5 mins to do it work and your sink will be gleaming ✨

This is the easiest way to clean your makeup sponges! 

Cleaning these sponges can be tricky! Sometimes it feels like they’ve got a whole bottle of foundation hiding in there 👀

If makeup brushes are more your tool of choice - head over and follow @lauracleanaholic for all the makeup brush cleaning tips you could ever need 🥰

This method will remove all that build up makeup & sanitise them at the same time: 

1. Pop your sponges into a bowl with tap water and add baby shampoo - ensure the sponges have absorbed the water. 

2. Place the bowl into the microwave for 4mins! 

3. Be super careful when removing the bowl as it will be piping hot! Use kitchen tongs to rinse them under water 🔥

4. Extra tip: for any stubborn stains add extra shampoo directly to the area & rinse! 

If you’ve go this far I have to be honest… I haven’t cleaned these sponges in about 6months 🫣 how long has it been since you cleaned yours?

The main 3 bathroom cleaning culprits! 

- Dust
I shared this tip I learnt a few months ago. Dust will cling to toilet paper leaving behind a surface which is much easier to clean. No more smearing dust around with a microfibre. 

- Water Marks 
Whether it be in the sink,shower or bath. They get everywhere! Cream cleaner will remove them with ease - give it a scrub and wash away the residue. 

- Limescale 
This is for all my hard water residents out there! Grab your favourite bathroom cleaner or some water vinegar and go to town with the toothbrush.

This one is for you! Cleaning white vinegar has so many uses but I often get asked how do you deal with the smell? Well it’s pretty easy to combat. 

In a spray bottle add half water & white vinegar and then add 10-15 drops of your favourite essential oils! 🫧

I wasn’t feeling 100% last week so that resulted in pretty much no cleaning & no cleaning means plenty of satisfying content so there’s always a silver lining somewhere😅

Lazy girls guide: white shoes 👟🫧

It was time to drag these out from under the mountain of shoes stored away in the cupboard. I’ve had my fair trial of white shoe cleaning - I’ve tried the washing machine,harsh chemicals and every thing in between by shoes always turned yellow 🥴 

Here are my white shoe cleaning tips: 

🫧 go with your most gentle detergent- you’ll be surprised how well it removes stains. 

🫧 always rinse your shoes afterwards. Leftover residue can leave your shoes turning yellow. 

🫧 do not dry them near or on a radiator. Drying them too quickly can cause them to turn yellow.

🫧 try to avoid direct sun! Again drying them too quickly can turn them yellow. 

🫧 if you want to help them dry quicker and for them to keep there shape stuff then with old cloths or socks. 

Now your summer ready! 🌞🌻🍉

After my quarterly cleaning top up it’s been so nice to have soda crystals back in the house again! Whenever I feature them in a reel I always get questions asking how to use them here are 3 ways I use them in the bathroom: 

💘 drain cleaning 
Oh don’t we all love the sight of the bathroom drain! Remove any debris from it, pour down a cup full and wash out with boiling water. 

💘 Grout cleaning
You may not instantly think of soda crystals for cleaning your grout as it’s a powder but once dampened it makes a great abrasive powder. 

💘 bring back fluffy towels 
A couple of cups of soda crystals in the washing machine with your towels and they’ll be feeling as good as new!

These are causing bad smells in your kitchen!🫣

In this heat odours are amplified but it’s finding that root cause of them which sends us on a Scooby doo style hunt 🕵🏼‍♀️

Jump in the mystery machine & let’s dive into those hidden odour causers: 

🧌 Drain catcher & drains:
If it wasn’t for @making_ahouse_ahome I wouldn’t have even known you could unscrew your drain catcher! And oh boy is it holding so unwanted muck! Give it a soak in your favourite disinfectant for half an hour and it will be as good as new ✨

Drains are an easy one : bicarb,your favourite disinfectant & hot water and those smells are gone 💥

🧌 Food Bin 
In this heat do yourself a favour and empty it every few days! Again disinfectant is your bestie, give it a pampering soak in the sink with your scent of choice. 

🧌 Extractor Fan Filter 
These are the definition of out of sight out of mind. The first time I ever did mine it was caked in grease 🫤 soda crystals,washing up liquid & boiling water that grease is gone 👋🏻

10mins to tidy 10mins to get messy again 🫠

With having an open plan kitchen you can see the mess from all angles. I use these 3 methods every morning to help keep on top of things. 

🫧 A clean sink is a clean kitchen in my eyes! Especially in hot weather nobody wants dishes stacked up on the counters. 

🫧 Fingerprints! Who’s idea was it to make appliances reflective? Standing at certain angels you can always see them! A quick wipe with some glass cleaner and it looks like you’ve done a much deeper clean. 

🫧 homeless clutter! My kitchen seems to be a breeding ground for clutter which doesn’t have a home. Putting away all those random items which have accumulated overnight really helps.
